    "summary": "Theoretical physicist working at Indian Institute of Technology, Kharagpur, India, under the supervision of Prof. Samudra Roy and Prof. Shailendra K. Varshney. My research work is based on light-matter interaction in third order nonlinear optical resonator system, emphasizing on soliton dynamics and frequency comb generation. Experienced in various numerical programming using MATLAB and structure modelling with COMSOL Multiphysics and Lumerical.     \n\nExperience:\n1. Strong expertise with nonlinear fibre optics, nonlinear optical cavity dynamics and analytical modelling.\n2. MATLAB\n3. LaTeX\n4. COMSOL Multiphysics\n5. Microsoft office\n6. Lumerical\n7. Fortran\n8. Microprocessor\n\nDegrees:\nBSc (Physics Honours): Scottish Church College, Calcutta. First division.\n\nMSc (Physics): University of Calcutta, Kolkata. First division.\n\nPhD (Photonics, Nonlinear Optics): Indian Institute of Technology, Kharagpur, India.\n\nAchievements:\n\n1.  INSPIRE Scholarship (Government of India) holder during BSc and MSc (2009- 2014).\n2.  GATE (2015): All India Rank- 116 (Physics).\n3.  MHRD fellowship (Government of India) holder in PhD (2015 -2020).\n\nResearch work Presentation:\n\n1.  Poster Presentation in Frontier in Optics (OSA) conference in Washington DC (2018).\n2. Oral Presentation in Photonics conference at IIT-Delhi (2018).\n\nTeaching experience:\n1. Physics 1st year Lab to B. tech students (IIT-Kharagpur, 2015-2019).\n2. MSc Physics lab (IIT-Kharagpur, 2015-2019).\n\nVolunteer experience:\n1. Smart India Hackathon, occurred at IIT-Kharagpur (2018, 2019).",
